gov.usgs.traveltime.session

Class TTSessionPool

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.traveltime.session.TTSessionPool

  • public class TTSessionPool
extends java.lang.Object
    This class will control handing out TTSessions and sharing them as needed. In its first form it always creates a new one and releases it when requested. The key for the session is the model and the depth to 2 sigfigs.

      • getTravelTimeSession

        public static TTSession getTravelTimeSession(java.lang.String model,
                                             double depth,
                                             java.lang.String[] phaseList,
                                             double lat,
                                             double lng,
                                             boolean allPhases,
                                             boolean backBranches,
                                             boolean tectonic,
                                             boolean rstt,
                                             boolean plot)
                                      throws java.io.IOException,
                                             java.lang.Exception
        Get a TTSession with the following model and settings. Once the caller has the model, the specifics can be changed by calling TTSession.newSession(). The session object remains the same, but the computations needed by the new settings are done.
        Parameters:
        model - Model name
        depth - Depth in km
        phaseList - If not null, an array with the desired phase
        lat - source Latitude in degrees
        lng - source Longitude in degrees
        allPhases - If true, calls return all phase
        backBranches - If true, call return back branches
        tectonic - Region is tectonic
        rstt - If true, use RSTT for local travel times
        plot - If true, this returns plot mode
        Returns:
        A TTSession set to the arguments
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If unable to read auxiliary or travel-time information
        java.lang.Exception
